'''Secrets''' in Dragon Warrior III (NES) include hidden features, optimal strategies, and game mechanics.

== Secret Locations ==

=== Hidden Shrine ===
A shrine containing the Sword of Kings.

'''Location:'''
* Accessible via Final Key
* Contains one of the best weapons

=== Navel of the Earth ===
The entrance to the final world.

'''Requirements:'''
* Defeat Baramos first
* Portal opens automatically
* Leads to Alefgard (Dragon Quest 1 world)

=== Rubiss Tower ===
Contains essential item for final boss.

'''Location:'''
* In Alefgard
* Sacred Amulet required
* Gives Sphere of Light

== Class Change System ==

=== Optimal Class Paths ===
Characters can change class at Dhama Temple:

'''Popular Builds:'''
* Soldier → Sage: Physical + Magic
* Wizard → Soldier: High MP fighter
* Pilgrim → Wizard: Versatile magic user

'''Requirements:'''
* Must be level 20+
* Visit Dhama Temple
* Stats halve but spells retained

=== Sage Creation ===
Two ways to create a Sage:
# Use Book of Satori on any class
# Level a Gadabout to 20 and class change

