== Hidden Items ==

=== Sword of Kings ===
One of the best weapons in the game.
* Found in hidden shrine
* Hero exclusive

=== Sage's Stone ===
Heals entire party when used.
* Found in Zoma's Castle
* Infinite uses

=== Staff of Rain ===
Required for Rainbow Drop.
* Shrine north of Aliahan

=== Crest of Rubiss ===
Essential for fighting Zoma.
* From Rubiss Tower in Alefgard

== Metal Slime Hunting ==

=== Metal Slime ===
* Location: Various mid-game areas
* High experience but flees quickly

=== Metal Babble ===
* Location: Alefgard dungeons
* Very high experience
* Even faster to flee

=== Hunting Tips ===
* Use critical-hit weapons
* High agility characters act first
* Accept low success rate

== Personality System (NES Notes) ==

The NES version has a basic personality system:
* Determined at character creation
* Affects stat growth patterns
* Less developed than later versions

== Alefgard Secrets ==

=== Tantegel Castle ===
* Home of descendant of Erdrick
* Starting area from Dragon Quest 1
* Contains useful items

=== Charlock Castle ===
* Former lair of Dragon Lord
* Now contains Zoma's minions
* Path to Zoma's Castle

=== Rimuldar ===
* Town from original game
* Equipment and information

== Tips ==

'''Party Composition:'''
* Hero required (cannot be removed)
* Sage is powerful but hard to create
* Balanced party recommended

'''Grinding:'''
* Levels 35-40 recommended for Zoma
* Metal enemies for fast experience
* Shrine areas for safe grinding

'''Final Boss:'''
* Use Sage's Stone for healing
* Sphere of Light removes Zoma's barrier
* Buff spells essential

== Known Issues ==

=== Save System ===
* Only one save file in NES version
* Password backup recommended
* Loss of progress permanent

=== Translation ===
* Some items/spells renamed from Japanese
* Certain NPC text abbreviated
* Quest objectives sometimes unclear

